The death has been an­nounced of a renowned community leader and church organiser, Madam Appolonia Iwudibia Okafor. She was aged 92. A native of Ebelano vil­lage, Egbuoma in Oguta Local Government Area of Imo state, the late Madam Iwudibia Okafor was very well regarded beyond her immediate environs due to an unyielding commitment to church activities. According to a burial pro­gramme signed on behalf of the family by her son, Nze Wilfred Iwudibia Okafor, mama’s final rites of passage would climax with a requi­em mass on Friday, April 9, 2021, at the St. Joseph Cath­olic Church, Egbuoma. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Thereafter, her remains will be buried at the family compound, while an outing Mass has been scheduled for Sunday, April 11, 2021 at Holy Trinity Catholic Church, Eg­buoma.